      "body":"### Buttons\r\n\r\n- [X] Buttons with pseudo selectors #119 -> #121\r\n- ~ opacities. (**EDIT** elaborated in #103) Deferring to the future until there are more use cases of opacity. Don't have enough confidence to make a good abstraction ATM.\r\n\r\n  1. Can only use pseudo selectors like `:&:hover` when using proper css, not inline.\r\n     - this disrupts the inline `+style` pattern we've been using\r\n  1. Can't use `with-styles` in proper css because it returns a nested map `{:style {}`} but\r\n  proper css wants a flat map\r\n     - There's an easy solution to this: `(:style (with-styles {})))`. But it's not pretty\r\n  1. Opacity is a pain because you aren't adding opacity to the element inline. Rather, you must\r\n  use the `opacify` function with the right color. Furthermore, you must find the opacity index.\r\n\r\n  The combination of all the above make buttons messy.\r\n\r\n### Mock Datoms\r\n- [X] Complete ##118  -> #120 \r\n\r\n  This isn't nearly as messy as buttons, just a few things left to do.\r\n\r\n  - Create helpers to let each DevCards easily instantiate its own DSDB\r\n  - Refactor helpers to let DevCards easily use real data, by pulling in an example db.",
